One might think the endless plains of [Kansas](/Kansas) offer little more than wheat fields and existential ennui, but even here, humanity’s persistent need to leave a mark has resulted in a rather extensive collection of historical remnants. Over 1,600 distinct [buildings](/Property_type_(National_Register_of_Historic_Places)), [sites](/Property_type_(National_Register_of_Historic_Places)), [districts](/Property_type_(National_Register_of_Historic_Places)), and [objects](/Property_type_(National_Register_of_Historic_Places)) have, for reasons best understood by bureaucrats and historians, earned a coveted spot on the [National Register of Historic Places](/National_Register_of_Historic_Places) in Kansas. A testament to, well, *something*, these listings span 101 of the state's [105 counties](/List_of_counties_in_Kansas). One can only wonder what fascinating lack of historical gravitas afflicts the remaining four.

